metadata.name: glory hole$ #366
metadata.description:
our consciousness as humans can be distilled into a crudely fashioned hole at an abandoned dave & busters and the meditative state that is endured while sitting on a neglected toilet praying for the sound of disrupted waters. glory holes embody anonymity and pleasure for pleasure's sake. they are creations that cannot be destroyed, as they exist in the memories of anyone who uses or witnesses. many speculate that the carving of the hole is the purest form of human ingenuity and the desire to explore the unknown. formerly limited to the physical space. these glory holes transcend space and time. and exist in that same unknown that tempts us all. legalize ground beef. create nothing. consume everything.

HUGE thank you to @PureSpider for the layered PNG template, this dream would not have been realized without you friend.

metadata.name: Perpetual Oscillations  #33
metadata.description:
Planes expand and contract over time in different rhythms. 

Display notes:
The work is intended to be viewed running live in the browser, and there is no set aspect ratio. The viewer is invited to explore the space and choose their viewpoint. 

Controls:
Left-clicking and dragging - rotate around the center 
right-clicking and dragging - pan around the space 
Scrolling - zoom in and out 
Press b - b-side 
Press o - go back to the origin 
Press 1 to 3 - change the pixel density
Adjusting pixel density or changing the screen size will bring you back to the origin. 

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Keep On #180
metadata.description:
One year ago, I published my first Fx(hash) work, "Finding my way". This piece marks its anniversary, and is intended as a THANK YOU to all the people that collected my works. 

It is based on the same algorithm as "Finding my way", i.e. a line growth animated process based on Substrate (Jared Tarbell, 2003) guided by dynamically changing vector fields made with trigonometric functions, but it uses different palettes, more vector fields, and a few more tweakings of the algorithm parameters.

The original piece was intended to symbolise a person's process of finding her/his way. Upon further reflections on the result, I think it more as representing a community process. So here is my wish for the Fx(hash) community, let's keep on finding our way.   

In what now could become a tradition, I've stolen again a palette from the beautiful work of Iskra Velitchkova.

Implemented using various packages from thi.ng/umbrella by Karsten Schmidt, AKA Toxi

metadata.name: 99 recorridos #26
THINK OUTSIDE THE BOX #53
metadata.description:
IMPORTANT: THE PIECES YOU MINT ARE NOT THE FULL ARTWORK.

This artwork relies on fxhash's gallery display to be viewed properly. It must be viewed with four pieces per line, and iterations from lowest to highest. You may need to resize the window to display the full project properly.

This piece is an experimental exploration of what lies beyond the canvas, told through counter-cultural slogans. Its nature is reflected in these chosen mottos, embodying the disdain for the old and the embrace of the new, unique and non-traditional style of this token. It's a call to arms for more avant-garde, experimental projects that push the limits of what we would currently consider generative art. Ignore the tried and true. Go against the grain. Think outside the box.

metadata.name: Currency 1.0 #139
metadata.description:
Currency 1.0

This is one of a series of conceptual artworks about art and valuation. Each artwork is an exact replica of itself, so all the generative pieces look and feel the same. This work references Fxhash & Tezos eco-system and thus each token is fictionally named as FXT, but it has no relation to the official platforms. 

This artwork attempts to questions the basic premise of art valuation - does art have any value if the art itself costs nothing? Is the value of art what the anyone wants to pay for the work? Is art itself the currency, or is currency the art?

There are 2500 editions in Currency 1.0, with each edition costing 0 XTZ. 
Royalty is 10%, the minimum permitted.

Currency 1.0 @beardcoded
